title: Roundup: Mason boys' win 10th straight
text:
Roundup: Mason boys' win 10th straight Cincinnati 10:54 p.m. EDT October 13, 2015 Buy Photo Rachel Royer of Oak Hills slides in on Olivia Polnow of Mason to try for the steal. The two teams played to a 0-0 tie. (Photo: Brandon Severn for the Enquirer) Buy Photo CONNECT 1 TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Mason won its 10th straight game Tuesday night in a 5-0 shutout over Oak Hills. 
Senior Evan Couchot led the No.1 ranked Rockets with two goals. Seniors Bryce Curran, Joseph Grimes and Kyle Bramwell each scored as well. 
Mason (14-0-2) finishes the regular season undefeated and will face either Edgewood or Wilmington in the first round of the playoffs. 
Indian Hills 6, Reading 0: Senior Carter Hoffman scored two goals to lead Indian Hills. 
Ross 3, Clark 0: Sophomore goalkeeper Michael Saylor recorded eight saves to shutout Clark. 
GIRLS' SOCCER 
Ross 7, Talawanda 0: Goalkeepers Katie Hansen and Camryn DiAngelo combined to shutout Talawanda. 
Seven different players scored for Ross. 
Harrison 6, Edgewood 0: Carah Kreimer and Eric Stevens each scored twice in the regular-season-finale. 
Goalkeeper Logan Lake recorded five saves for the shutout. Harrison finishes the regular season ranked No. 10 in the Division I coaches' poll. 
Lakota West 2, Hamilton 0: Lakota West goalkeeper Maddie Jewell recorded four saves in a shutout win. 
Abby Prohaska and Devin Duhme each scored. Read or Share this story: http://cin.ci/1RGs4lE TOP VIDEOS
